text.tspan: Workshop on Python in High Energy Physics
PyHEP is a series of workshops initiated and supported by the
HEP Software Foundation (HSF) to discuss and promote the
use of Python in the HEP community.
PyHEP 2020 will be held on the University of Texas at Austin
campus, right next door to SciPy 2020, the primary conference
for the scientific Python community at large. SciPy 2020 will be
held on July 6‒12, making it easy to attend both.
• a keynote presentation from the Data Science domain
• follow-ups on the topics from PyHEP 2019.
All Python skill levels are welcome!
Matthew Feickert — University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign
Peter Onyisi — The University of Texas at Austin
